a ray://ray-head:10001, prints pong\n  kube-root-ca.crt (key: ca.crt)   - Standard Kubernetes cluster CA certificate (auto-injected)\n\n========================================================\n2. DEVIATIONS FROM BASELINE / DEFAULT VALUES\n========================================================\n\nDEVIATION 1 — Dashboard enabled on ray-head (HIGH visibility)\n  Baseline (last-applied-configuration): --include-dashboard=false\n  Current:                               --include-dashboard=true --dashboard-host=0.0.0.0\n  Evidence: Deployment revision 2; last-applied shows false, live spec shows true.\n  The dashboard listens on 0.0.0.0:8265 inside the pod and is reachable at\n  ClusterIP 10.96.161.182:8265 from within the cluster.\n\nDEVIATION 2 — ray-worker scaled from 2 to 3 replicas (INTENTIONAL capacity change)\n  Baseline (last-applied-configuration): replicas: 2\n  Current:                               replicas: 3\n  Evidence: Deployment revision 2; last-applied shows replicas=2, live spec=3.\n  All 3 worker pods are ready and available.\n\nDEVIATION 3 — ray-head Service exposes dashboard (8265) and client (10001) ports\n  Baseline: Service had only port gcs/6379 in last-applied-configuration.\n  Current:  Three ports: gcs/6379, dashboard/8265, client/10001.\n  This aligns with Deviation 1 (dashboard enabled) and allows ray.init(address=\n  \"ray://ray-head:10001\") from within the cluster (as used by ray-job-script).\n\nDEVIATION 4 — No resource requests or limits on either deployment (RISK)\n  Both ray-head and ray-worker have resources: {} on their containers.\n  This places all pods in the BestEffort QoS class. Under node memory pressure,\n  these pods are the FIRST candidates for OOM eviction by the kubelet.\n  The change-plan ConfigMap proposes adding limits; none have been applied yet.\n\n========================================================\n3. COMPLIANCE NOTES AND RECOMMENDATIONS\n========================================================\n\n[REC-1] Add CPU and memory requests/limits (Priority: HIGH)\n  BestEffort pods can be evicted without warning under node pressure.\n  The existing change-plan ConfigMap already documents proposed values:\n    ray-head:   cpu=500m/1000m, memory=512Mi/1Gi\n    ray-worker: cpu=500m/2000m, memory=1Gi/2Gi\n  Apply during the next change window per the documented order in change-plan.\n\n[REC-2] Review dashboard network exposure (Priority: MEDIUM)\n  The dashboard is bound to 0.0.0.0 inside the pod and reachable via ClusterIP.\n  Access is currently limited to within the cluster (no NodePort/LoadBalancer).\n  Confirm this is intentional and that no NetworkPolicy is required to restrict\n  which pods/namespaces may reach 10.96.161.182:8265.\n  If external browser access is not needed, consider reverting to\n  --include-dashboard=false to reduce the attack surface.\n\n[REC-3] Image version currency (Priority: LOW)\n  Both deployments run rayproject/ray:2.9.0. The change-plan targets 2.10.0.\n  Verify that 2.10.0 contains relevant CVE patches before the upgrade window.\n  Pin to a digest (e.g. rayproject/ray:2.10.0@sha256:...) for reproducibility.\n\n[REC-4] Worker replica scaling plan (Priority: LOW)\n  Workers were scaled from 2 → 3 (current). The change-plan proposes 3 → 4.\n  Confirm the target node has sufficient allocatable CPU before scaling further,\n  especially once resource requests are added (each worker will reserve 500m CPU).\n\n[REC-5] ray-job-script and change-plan ConfigMaps (Priority: INFO)\n  These are non-system ConfigMaps present in the namespace:\n  - ray-job-script: a simple smoke-test job; harmless, can be retained.\n  - change-plan: the pending upgrade plan; ensure it is updated to reflect any\n    out-of-band changes before the window opens.\n\n========================================================\nEND OF AUDIT — NO CHANGES WERE MADE TO THE CLUSTER\n========================================================\nEOF\n)\" 2>&1","description":"Create config-audit